## 🗃️ Data Model

The Power BI semantic model follows a **star schema** design:

```
dim_date ──────────┐
dim_hour ──────────┤
dim_season ────────┼──── fact_bike_rentals (view)
dim_weather ───────┤
dim_user_type ─────┘
```

- **`dim_user_type`** is a custom dimension created to support Casual vs Registered segmentation across all visuals
- The fact table was unpivoted from wide format (separate casual/registered columns) to long format (one row per rental event per user type) to enable proper star schema relationships
- **`forecast_output`** is a standalone CSV-sourced table connected to the date dimension for forecast visualization

