## 📈 Key DAX Measures

```dax
-- Core rental aggregations
Total Rentals = SUM('public view_fact_bike_rentals'[rentals])
Casual Rentals = CALCULATE([Total Rentals], 'dim_user_type'[user_type_label] = "Casual User")
Registered Rentals = CALCULATE([Total Rentals], 'dim_user_type'[user_type_label] = "Registered User")
Casual Pct = DIVIDE([Casual Rentals], [Total Rentals], 0)

-- Year-over-year growth
YoY % Change =
VAR CurrentYear  = MAX('public view_fact_bike_rentals'[year])
VAR CurrentMonth = MAX('public view_fact_bike_rentals'[month_num])
VAR CurrentPeriod = CALCULATE(SUM('public view_fact_bike_rentals'[rentals]))
VAR PriorPeriod =
    CALCULATE(
        SUM('public view_fact_bike_rentals'[rentals]),
        REMOVEFILTERS('public view_fact_bike_rentals'[year]),
        REMOVEFILTERS('public dim_date'),
        'public view_fact_bike_rentals'[year]      = CurrentYear - 1,
        'public view_fact_bike_rentals'[month_num] = CurrentMonth
    )
RETURN IF(ISBLANK(PriorPeriod), BLANK(), DIVIDE(CurrentPeriod - PriorPeriod, PriorPeriod))

-- Forecast KPIs
Actual Last 12 Months =
VAR MaxDate = CALCULATE(MAX('public view_fact_bike_rentals'[dteday]), REMOVEFILTERS('public view_fact_bike_rentals'))
VAR StartDate = EDATE(MaxDate, -12)
RETURN
    CALCULATE(
        SUM('public view_fact_bike_rentals'[rentals]),
        FILTER(ALL('public dim_date'),
            'public dim_date'[dteday] > StartDate &&
            'public dim_date'[dteday] <= MaxDate)
    )
```

